A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Declaration of Rights – Right to Minimum Wage for Tipped Workers
3 FOR the purpose of establishing that every person, as a central component of an
4 individual’s right to liberty and equality, has the fundamental right while engaged
5 in employment in the State with respect to which the payment of a tip is customary,
6 to be paid at a wage rate that is at least equal to the State minimum wage rate set
7 by law without regard to tips that the individual receives; and prohibiting the State
8 from, directly or indirectly, denying, burdening, or abridging the right unless
9 justified by a compelling State interest achieved by the least restrictive means.
10 BY proposing an addition to the Maryland Constitution
11 Declaration of Rights
12 Article 49
13 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
14 (Three–fifths of all the members elected to each of the two Houses concurring), That it be
15 proposed that the Maryland Constitution read as follows:
16 Declaration of Rights
17 ARTICLE 49.
18 THAT EVERY PERSON, AS A CENTRAL COMPONENT OF AN INDIVIDUAL’S RIGHT
19 TO LIBERTY AND EQUALITY, HAS THE FUNDAMENTAL RIGHT WHILE ENGAGED IN
20 EMPLOYMENT IN THE STATE WITH RESPECT TO WHICH THE PAYMENT OF A TIP IS
21 CUSTOMARY, TO BE PAID AT A WAGE RATE THAT IS AT LEAST EQUAL TO THE STATE
22 MINIMUM WAGE RATE SET BY LAW WITHOUT REGARD TO TIPS THAT THE INDIVIDUAL
23 RECEIVES. THE STATE MAY NOT, DIRECTLY OR INDIRECTLY, DENY, BURDEN, OR
24 ABRIDGE THE RIGHT UNLESS JUSTIFIED BY A COMPELLING STATE INTEREST
25 ACHIEVED BY THE LEAST RESTRICTIVE MEANS.
